wiki.summary: "Rover" is a song recorded by South Korean singer Kai for his third extended play of the same name. It was released as the EP's lead single by SM Entertainment on March 13, 2023. The track was composed by Cristian Tarcea, Dara, Valentina Nikova, YNGA, Gabriel Brandes and Young Chance, with the arrangement held by Tarcea and Imlay. It is remake of Bulgarian singer Dara's original song titled "Mr. Rover", Described as a dancehall song with heavy bass, marimba, bells and various percussion instruments. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Rover" is a song recorded by South Korean singer Kai for his third extended play of the same name. It was released as the EP's lead single by SM Entertainment on March 13, 2023. The track was composed by Cristian Tarcea, Dara, Valentina Nikova, YNGA, Gabriel Brandes and Young Chance, with the arrangement held by Tarcea and Imlay. It is remake of Bulgarian singer Dara's original song titled "Mr. Rover", Described as a dancehall song with heavy bass, marimba, bells and various percussion instruments. The lyrics, which was written by Park Tae-won, discuss freeing oneself from the restraints of others' viewpoints and living freely as a "wanderer". The song was composed in the key of C# minor, with a tempo of 186 beats per minute. Read more on Last.fm.
